window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>New York Times</i></b><b> bestselling and Newbery Medal-winning author Neil Gaiman’s modern classic, </b><b><i>Coraline</i></b><b>—also an Academy Award-nominated film</b></p> <p><i>\"Coraline discovered the door a little while after they moved into the house....\"</i></p> <p>When Coraline steps through a door to find another house strangely similar to her own (only better), things seem marvelous.</p> <p>But there's another mother there, and another father, and they want her to stay and be their little girl. They want to change her and never let her go.</p> <p>Coraline will have to fight with all her wit and courage if she is to save herself and return to her ordinary life.</p> <p>Neil Gaiman's <i>Coraline </i>is a can't-miss classic that enthralls listeners age 8 to 12 but also adults who enjoy a perfect smart spooky listen.</p>"; 
